"{\"uid\": \"royalgazette.com-opinion-writer-opinion-article-20240809-two-bermudas-from-olympics-to-politics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Bermuda, with its picturesque landscapes and vibrant culture, presents a fa\\u00e7ade of unity and prosperity.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its picturesque landscapes\", \"from\": 14, \"to\": 40}, {\"ngram\": \"vibrant culture\", \"from\": 45, \"to\": 60}, {\"ngram\": \"a fa\\u00e7ade\", \"from\": 71, \"to\": 79}, {\"ngram\": \"unity\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 88}, {\"ngram\": \"prosperity\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 103}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, beneath this surface lies a stark divide in the lived realities of Bermudians.\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.316231486018017e-18, \"text\": \"Bermudians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this surface\", \"from\": 124, \"to\": 136}, {\"ngram\": \"a stark divide\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 156}, {\"ngram\": \"the lived realities\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This division has never been more pronounced to me than in our national representation at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 299, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This division\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 209}, {\"ngram\": \"our national representation\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 282}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 298}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Out of the team of eight Olympians, fewer than three are Black, and even fewer attended public school or completed their secondary education in Bermuda.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 444, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 315}, {\"ngram\": \"eight Olympians\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"even fewer attended public school\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 401}, {\"ngram\": \"their secondary education\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From an outsider's perspective, it might appear that Bermuda's population is predominantly White and privately educated.\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 506, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an outsider's perspective\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, this is far from the truth.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 606, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 605}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only 30 per cent of our population is White and less than 50 per cent have been privately educated.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only 30 per cent\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"our population\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"less than 50 per cent\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What is causing this disparity?\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this disparity\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it is rooted in the inequitable admiration and reverence awarded to those who graduate from private schools, boarding schools or alike.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the inequitable admiration\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"reverence\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"private schools\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"boarding schools\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I attended public school for most of my academic years, and the quality of education I received was on par with, if not better than, that offered at some private schools on the island.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"public school\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"my academic years\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"education\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"par\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"some private schools\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, when it comes to prestigious opportunities such as the Rhodes Scholarship, participating in and leading the National Youth Policy Working Group, representing Bermuda at Commonwealth conferences, being celebrated as \\\"Bermudian young leader\\\" and similar opportunities, privately educated young people seem to have a distinct advantage.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhodes_Scholarship\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhodes Scholarship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhodes_Scholarship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhodes_Scholarship\"}, {\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_of_Nations\", \"score\": 0.999881248504812, \"rank\": 0.00011873842980615173, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_of_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_of_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7862645605247754e-20, \"text\": \"Bermudian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"prestigious opportunities\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"the National Youth Policy Working Group\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1218}, {\"ngram\": \"similar opportunities\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"privately educated young people\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"a distinct advantage\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, I published a post on LinkedIn after attending the Annual Dinner of the Bermuda Society.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1441, \"end\": 1449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LinkedIn\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a post\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"the Annual Dinner\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bermuda Society\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is my LinkedIn post in full that underscores this point: \\\"Yesterday I had the pleasure of attending The Bermuda Society's 34th Annual Dinner as a guest of the Government of Bermuda.\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1519, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LinkedIn\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pleasure\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"The Bermuda Society's 34th Annual Dinner\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"a guest\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"the Government\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"Bermuda\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an honour to be in the presence of such great company, especially two of my fellow former Youth Parliamentarians, McKenzie-Kohl H. Tuckett and Ywione Darrell.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_England\", \"score\": 0.8970657552086125, \"rank\": 0.11474485365185129, \"text\": \"Parliamentarians\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an honour\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"such great company\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"McKenzie-Kohl H. Tuckett\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"Ywione Darrell\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thank Brandon Sousa at the Bermuda London Office and Sheba Raza from the Bermuda Society for the invitation.\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Little_and_associates\", \"score\": 0.999561278201516, \"rank\": 0.0004389141073335778, \"text\": \"Brandon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Little_and_associates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Little_and_associates\"}, {\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Philip_Sousa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.069671558352914e-15, \"text\": \"Sousa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Philip_Sousa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Philip_Sousa\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999996334496007, \"rank\": 2.0501702794237782e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_of_Sheba\", \"score\": 0.9996637558505419, \"rank\": 0.0003363196642250959, \"text\": \"Sheba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_of_Sheba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_of_Sheba\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Raza\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7920674539997152e-23, \"text\": \"Raza\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Raza\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Raza\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the invitation\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bermuda's young people are doing great things!\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 2019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"great things\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, in the midst of eating the lovely dinner prepared and served to us by the staff at the Armours Hall, I was struck with the stark realisation that while I was one of 13 students in attendance, I was the only graduate from the Bermuda public school system.\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the midst\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"the lovely dinner\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2071}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"the staff\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"the Armours Hall\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the stark realisation\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"13 students\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"attendance\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"the only graduate\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And when I attend events such as these, I am constantly reminded how lucky I am to be one of the chosen few, as these kinds of opportunities are not often made available to students from our public schools.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"these kinds\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"opportunities\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2426}, {\"ngram\": \"students\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"our public schools\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, let me propose this: I should not have to be lucky to be invited into these spaces.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these spaces\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Bermuda public school system has not been the kindest to me as an openly queer student, the education I received was on par with, if not better than, that being offered at Bermuda's many private schools.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2598, \"end\": 2605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}, {\"begin\": 2770, \"end\": 2777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an openly queer student\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"the education\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"par\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A testament to this: I can name many of my public-school peers who are wildly more successful, equally as brilliant, but are forced to work ten times as hard just to get a seat at the same table that is often offered to many private-school students just on the basis of who they are, who they know and where they were educated.\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my public-school peers\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2866}, {\"ngram\": \"a seat\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2980}, {\"ngram\": \"the same table\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"many private-school students\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With that said, if we truly aim to bring Bermuda forward, we must ensure our public-school students are afforded the same opportunities as private-school students.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3175, \"end\": 3182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our public-school students\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"the same opportunities\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3269}, {\"ngram\": \"private-school students\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lastly, I am reminded of a quote used during Franco Harris's Toast to Bermuda last night: 'The true measure of any society can be found in how it treats its most vulnerable members.'\\\"\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3343, \"end\": 3349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francisco_Franco\", \"score\": 0.992227332938117, \"rank\": 0.007748926342860185, \"text\": \"Franco\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francisco_Franco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francisco_Franco\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a quote\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"Bermuda\", \"from\": 3368, \"to\": 3375}, {\"ngram\": \"The true measure\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3405}, {\"ngram\": \"any society\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"its most vulnerable members\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After my post, nothing much has changed in terms of those who are invited and the demographics of young people who make up the Junior Bermuda Society.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3617, \"end\": 3624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my post\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3496}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3505}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3531}, {\"ngram\": \"the demographics\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"young people\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I expected as much because this somewhat elusive organisation, just like our Olympic team, is representative of the image Bermuda likes to portray of itself to world.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3756, \"end\": 3763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this somewhat elusive organisation\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3695}, {\"ngram\": \"our Olympic team\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3723}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3755}, {\"ngram\": \"world\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic team, composed predominantly of athletes who are visibly White and privately educated, does not mirror the racial and socioeconomic composition of Bermuda.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3960, \"end\": 3967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic team\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3817}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 3853}, {\"ngram\": \"the racial and socioeconomic composition\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 3956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The disparities in education stem from and feed directly into the broader issues of race and class in a vicious cycle.\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 4088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The disparities\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3985}, {\"ngram\": \"education\", \"from\": 3989, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"the broader issues\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4050}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4058}, {\"ngram\": \"class\", \"from\": 4063, \"to\": 4068}, {\"ngram\": \"a vicious cycle\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In my high school, The Berkeley Institute, the number of White students could be counted on two hands.\", \"from\": 4089, \"to\": 4191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4108, \"end\": 4130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Berkeley_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Berkeley Institute\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Berkeley_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Berkeley_Institute\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my high school\", \"from\": 4092, \"to\": 4106}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4142}, {\"ngram\": \"White students\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"two hands\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This demographic imbalance in public schools reflects the socioeconomic divide within Bermuda.\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4278, \"end\": 4285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3271187023748916e-18, \"text\": \"Bermuda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This demographic imbalance\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4218}, {\"ngram\": \"public schools\", \"from\": 4222, \"to\": 4236}, {\"ngram\": \"the socioeconomic divide\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Public schools predominantly serve Black and lower-income students, while private schools cater to a more affluent, and often whiter, non-Bermudian demographic.\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Public schools\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4301}, {\"ngram\": \"Black and lower-income students\", \"from\": 4322, \"to\": 4353}, {\"ngram\": \"private schools\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4376}, {\"ngram\": \"non-Bermudian demographic\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This segregation creates a cycle of inequality where access to high-quality education and prestigious opportunities is unequally distributed.\", \"from\": 4448, \"to\": 4589, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This segregation\", \"from\": 4448, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"a cycle\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4480}, {\"ngram\": \"inequality\", \"from\": 4484, \"to\": 4494}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4507}, {\"ngram\": \"high-quality education\", \"from\": 4511, \"to\": 4533}, {\"ngram\": \"prestigious opportunities\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This disparity extends into politics.\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4628, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This disparity\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4605}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former Progressive Labour Party leader Marc Bean has made several assertions that cast a critical light on the PLP.\", \"f