d\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_supremacy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_supremacy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its roots\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4787}, {\"ngram\": \"labour\", \"from\": 4791, \"to\": 4797}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 4817, \"to\": 4827}, {\"ngram\": \"values\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This accusation is particularly resonant when considering both the ever-present and deepening divide between the two Bermudas and that many of the PLP's present leaders, including the Premier and the Minister of Education, attended private school.\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 5141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5011, \"end\": 5019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9965086078190798e-18, \"text\": \"Bermudas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}, {\"begin\": 5041, \"end\": 5044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6283848200586072e-13, \"text\": \"PLP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This accusation\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 4909}, {\"ngram\": \"both the ever-present and deepening divide\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 4994}, {\"ngram\": \"the Premier\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5085}, {\"ngram\": \"the Minister\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5102}, {\"ngram\": \"Education\", \"from\": 5106, \"to\": 5115}, {\"ngram\": \"private school\", \"from\": 5126, \"to\": 5140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How can the PLP claim to be a party for the people when many of its leaders were educated in an isolated, elite part of the Bermudian community?\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5155, \"end\": 5158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6283848200586072e-13, \"text\": \"PLP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5267, \"end\": 5276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7862645605247754e-20, \"text\": \"Bermudian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bermuda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a party\", \"from\": 5171, \"to\": 5178}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 5183, \"to\": 5193}, {\"ngram\": \"its leaders\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So there may be some validity to Mr Bean's claims after all ... let us examine further.\", \"from\": 5289, \"to\": 5376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5322, \"end\": 5329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.911762962019524e-26, \"text\": \"Mr Bean\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some validity\", \"from\": 5305, \"to\": 5318}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 5357, \"to\": 5359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The PLP's shift from its original purpose to a more capitalist and elitist stance, as highlighted by Walton Brown in his book,Bermuda and the Struggles for Reform: Race Politics & Ideology, indicates a significant ideological shift.\", \"from\": 5378, \"to\": 5610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5382, \"end\": 5385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6283848200586072e-13, \"text\": \"PLP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliamentary_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5479, \"end\": 5485, \"title\"